11:35 AM Attorney Ryan Anthony Reid in court for Cheyenne Lee Androsky.  Attorney Mark Adam Fruehauf in court for State of Wisconsin. Defendant Cheyenne Lee Androsky not in court. 
Att. Reid- Spoke with client this morning. Expected her to be here. Checks hall.
State- requests warrant and bond forfeited. Has witness here
Att. Reid- Client had indicated she would be a little late
Court orders warrant and bond forfeited. Wisconsin and MN
Clerk is notified she is in the parking lot right now
State- will wait a couple of minutes
11:38 recalled
Court quashes warrant
State calls Bradley Jago- sworn and testifies. Officer for SPD. Was involved in search warrant execution. Stopped a vehicle  with defendant relative to that warrant. Found meth in her sweatshirt pocket. 
Att. Reid cross examines. Substance tested positive for MDMA/meth. She stated item wasn't hers.
State moves for bind over
Att Reid- Objects to bind over. Possess MDMA is a misdemeanor in Wisconsin. 
Court finds probable cause for bind over. Sets arraignment date. Questions late appearance
Att Reid. Her ride from Solon Springs was delayed by law enforcement before picking her up. 
Court questions why she is going to Solon Springs on her court date
Att Reis- is now living back with her mother at Biller Loop Rd in Solon Springs
Court notes she notified Clerk she had different address on 9/1/22
Att. Reid- she is now back at Solon Springs address
State- will not be asking for increase in bail
Court cautions defendant to appear on time
Arraignment scheduled for November 22, 2022 at 08:30 am.
